  "verdict": "QUALIFIED REPLICATION -- and the qualification is the finding. (1) STRUCTURE fires: N2-vs-REM discrimination in 14/15 recordings [N=15 recordings from 8 subjects, both nights; not fully independent.] confirming Trilha A1 on a second paradigm (median structural ratio 2.79). (2) PRE-REGISTERED POWER ARM (within-N2 high-vs-low natural power) is NOT silent: only 3/15 fall below the 1.5 bar (median natural-power ratio 1.89), so by the pre-registered criterion the clean appendix dissociation does NOT replicate on sleep. (3) POST-HOC DIAGNOSIS (added after seeing (2), labelled as such): a pure-amplitude control -- two random N2 halves, which a per-window gain leaves geometrically identical -- IS silent in 12/15 recordings (median pure-amplitude ratio 1.00), so the geometry IS power-blind by construction. The natural-power non-silence is therefore GENUINE STRUCTURE, not a power-blindness failure: high-power N2 epochs carry more spindles/slow-wave structure than low-power ones, and the geometry correctly detects it. HONEST CONCLUSION: the structure-vs-power dissociation holds at the mechanism level (silent on pure amplitude, fires on structure, clean gap 2.79 vs 1.00), but the appendix's clean 'silent on a NATURAL power transition' is PARADIGM-SPECIFIC -- it holds only when the paradigm's power change preserves spatial structure (occipital rest/movement) and fails when power and structure are naturally confounded (sleep within-stage). A real qualification the single-paradigm appendix could not expose. Pre-registered outcome tag: FIRES-but-natural-power-NOT-SILENT.",
